1. Title

Automated Application Deployment Using AWS CodePipeline and CodeDeploy

2. Objective

To design and implement an automated CI/CD pipeline that deploys a web application to a Windows EC2 instance using AWS managed services.

3. Architecture

Amazon S3 (Source)

AWS CodePipeline (Orchestration)

AWS CodeDeploy (Deployment)

Windows EC2 (Hosting)

4. Tools & Services Used

Amazon S3

AWS CodePipeline

AWS CodeDeploy

Amazon EC2

IAM

Security Groups

5. Implementation Steps

(Use the step-by-step explanation already provided)

6. Result

The application was successfully deployed automatically, and the web page was accessible via public IP.

7. Conclusion

This project demonstrates a real-world CI/CD implementation using AWS services and highlights automation, security, and scalability.

üß™ COMMON ERRORS & FIXES (VERY IMPORTANT)
‚ùå Error: Pipeline Source Stage Fails

Cause: S3 versioning disabled
Fix: Enable versioning on S3 bucket

‚ùå Error: Deployment Failed

Cause: CodeDeploy agent not running
Fix: Restart agent on EC2

Start-Service codedeployagent

‚ùå Error: Website Not Opening

Cause: Port 80 blocked
Fix: Allow HTTP in security group

‚ùå Error: EC2 Not Found in Deployment Group

Cause: Missing IAM role
Fix: Attach EC2CodeDeployRole to instance

‚ùå Error: Access Denied

Cause: Incorrect IAM policy
Fix: Attach correct AWS managed policies
